content.description:
The Sunny Side Arete - 5.10c ** (45') F(5b)

Harder than it looks! Start at the left end of the south face of the main dihedral, and climb the arete through increasingly difficult moves to the tricky final crux to reach the chains on top.
content.location: Climbs the right edge of the main arete (the left edge of the main south face of the main dihedral).

content.description:
Stress Test - 5.10c** (50') F(6b)

Climbs the middle of the West face that is on the right end of the crag. The rock is dirty and somewhat hollow and brittle (the anchors are all on solid rock), but the climbing is interesting and sustained.
content.protection: Fixed - 6 bolts to 2 chain anchors on the lip.
content.location: Climbs the middle of the West face right of the obvious inside corner.

content.description:
Ides of March - 5.10 ** (45') (M(2b)

Climbs the right side of the The Sunny Side Face, beginning at the inside corner and ending on the bulge above the vertical crack. Harder than it looks, starts easy and gets progressively harder to end with the desperate bolt protected bulge just below the chains.
content.protection: Mixed - 2 bolts and a wide range of cams, from #0 to 4. Chain anchors on top.
content.location: Climbs the obvious crack on the right side of The Sunny Side face.

content.description:
Gates of Delirium - 5.10b*** (45') F(6b)

Climbs the middle of the face on the left side of the crag. Sustained and interesting well protected climbing on mostly good rock leads to the high crux before the chain anchors.
content.location: In the middle of the left (north) face of the crag.
